    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's more than just \"symbolism\" though. when you look at the actual alignment of the obelisk at the center and how the avenues radiate out toward the specific monuments, it feels like they are directing something. like a flow of energy or intent. do you think the specific shape of those intersections could have been designed to influence the people walking through them? like a way to subconsciously control how they feel or act?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
